h4. Summary
Adding in {{-Dupm.pac.disable=true}} to JVM parameters does not stop Jira from connecting to the Marketplace as indicated in [problems connecting to the Atlassian marketplace|https://confluence.atlassian.com/upm/problems-connecting-to-the-atlassian-marketplace-273875718.html].

While this works for Confluence.

h4. Steps to reproduce 
# Set {{-Dupm.pac.disable=true}} in setenv.sh or Windows Service Java Options (depends which OS is running Jira).
# Start Jira
# Navigate to *Jira Administration* > *Add ons*

h4. Expected results
*Find new apps* should not appear or allow searching of apps in marketplace.

h4. Actual results
*Find new apps* is present and connecting to the marketplace, searching and downloading plugins and updates work as normal.

h4. Verify 
You can verify if its disabled without going to Find new apps via - http://yourjira/rest/plugins/1.0/settings

Results shows -
{code}
{"settings":[{"key":"pacDisabled","value":false,"requiresRefresh":true,"defaultCheckedValue":true,"readOnly":false},{"key":"requestsDisabled","value":false,"requiresRefresh":true,"defaultCheckedValue":true,"readOnly":false},{"key":"emailDisabled","value":false,"requiresRefresh":false,"defaultCheckedValue":true,"readOnly":false},{"key":"autoUpdateEnabled","value":false,"requiresRefresh":false,"defaultCheckedValue":false,"readOnly":false}]}
{code}
Where {{"pacDisabled","value":false}} value false shows that it was not disabling pac.

While in start up parameters show that -Dupm.pac.disable=true is set in the application logs -
{code}
upm.pac.disable                               : true
{code}

In Confluence this works and shows results -
{code}
{"settings":[{"key":"pacDisabled","value":true,"requiresRefresh":true,"defaultCheckedValue":true,"readOnly":false},{"key":"requestsDisabled","value":false,"requiresRefresh":true,"defaultCheckedValue":true,"readOnly":false},{"key":"emailDisabled","value":false,"requiresRefresh":false,"defaultCheckedValue":true,"readOnly":false},{"key":"autoUpdateEnabled","value":false,"requiresRefresh":false,"defaultCheckedValue":false,"readOnly":false}]}
{code}
Where {{"pacDisabled","value":true}}

Tested on UPM versions 2.22.9, 2.22.14, 2.22.19, 3.0.1

h4. Workaround
Can only disable this in Jira via *Jira Administration* > *Add ons* > *Manage apps* go to the settings and *uncheck* the *Connect to the Atlassian Marketplace* option.

h3. Summary
After a Project import of a JIRA Software Scrum project, the Epic report will not be generated. The root cause of the problem is Jira is not setting correct Epic Link history items during project import.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Perform a Project import of a JIRA Software Scrum project.
# Crosscheck the Epic report between the Source and Target - Target instance will not generate the Epic report graph on the page.

h3. Expected Results
Epic report to be generated as per the Source instance.
!source.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Actual Results
The page returns a blank graph:
!target.png|thumbnail! 

h3.Workaround
# Grab the issue id and issue key of the epic you want to fix
# Execute the following queries:
{noformat}
update changeitem set newvalue = <EPIC ISSUE ID> where newstring = <EPIC ISSUE KEY>;
update changeitem set oldvalue = <EPIC ISSUE ID> where oldstring = <EPIC ISSUE KEY>;
{noformat}
(i) For example, if the epic key is {{SSP1-53}} and the epic issue id is {{10049}}:
{noformat}
update changeitem set newvalue = 10049 where newstring = 'SSP1-53';
update changeitem set oldvalue = 10049 where oldstring = 'SSP1-53';
{noformat}
# Perform a project reindex.

I'm able to create several different types of issues (all being what's accepted in the Admin section under the particular project in question).  However, i am not able to create an "Epic" as its inner exception's error response reads:  

 

{"errorMessages":[],"errors":\{"customfield_10003":"Epic Name is required."}}

 

Any help as to a work-around for this issue in the API?
